            <span class="dropcap"> H </span> Tomorrow we got up in dry weather. Unfortunately, that shouldn't stay that way.
            I had heard / read somewhere that there should be Delphine in the Bay of Ballina, which should sometimes even come very close to the beach. Since the beach starts right on the other side of the street, I sent nuts with the camera while preparing the car for the onward journey. </p>
		<p> Unfortunately, dolphins were not in the bay this morning, but already some pelicans. They once again waited for some fishermen to finish cleaning their catch and that they can get the remains. After I checked out, I took a few steps to the beach to look at my spectacle. Then we made our way. </p>
		<p> It shouldn't go far today. Just a little more than 100km to Surfers Paradise. There are 3 things I would like to do. </p>
		<ol>
			<li> Go for a walk on the promenade with nuts </li>
			<li> To the hard rock cafe, buy shirts </li>
			<li> On the Qeck. Viewing deck to 77. And 78th floor of the Q1 Tower </li>
		</ol>

