		<p> On the way there we wanted to drive past one or the other viewing platform again, hoping to see a whale. At the Lenox Head we could even make a difference in the distance that a jumping whale could have been. So we decided to continue driving to Byron Bay and our luck there again. </p>
		<p> Unfortunately, it started on the way there how to pour out of buckets. So in Byron Bay we decided not to leave the dry security of our vans and to hope for better weather north. </p>
		<p> Once in Surfer's paradise, it looked shortly afterwards as if it stopped raining.
			So we quickly looked for a covered parking lot and started looking for the hard rock cafe. 
			On the way there we came to a shopping center from which you can look at the promenade. 
			With this foresight, unfortunately we had to look at the reality that told us that it would probably not stop raining.
			At least not in the next few minutes. </p>
		<p> When I arrived at Hard Rock Cafe, I was lucky enough to meet the boss back personally. 
			A few weeks ago, I had accidentally met you at the HRC in Sydney and she promised me at the time to put a shirt in my size aside. ;) </p>
