		<p> Since the sky had just scored all the goals again, we chatted a little with her and a nice employee who then gave us the order to greet a Kiwi colleague in the Hamburg Hard Rock Cafe. </p>
        <p> After a while we made our way back to the car. On the way through the city, we then decided to drop the other two points on my list and simply continue to Brisbane. We just don't feel like rain anymore. </p>
		<p> In Brisbane, the Big4 campsite was full again. 
			But it's not that bad today, because tomorrow morning we want to go to the workshop first to have the shock absorbers exchanged.
			The current ones are a bit spongy and the highway is over just behind Brisbane. 
			We don't know what the streets look like. </p>
		<p> So we are now making it comfortable in the parking lot of a petrol station with meat sausage and cheese. </p>
